  "instructions": [
    "Preheat broiler. Season ground beef with salt and pepper.",
    "Sauté minced garlic in a large skillet until fragrant, about 1 minute.",
    "Add onions, bell peppers, and cinnamon; stir-fry for 5 minutes or until the vegetables are translucent.",
    "Mix in ground beef, lemon juice from all lemons (6 oz), chicken broth, lime juice, salt, and pepper. Stir well to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer. Reduce heat to medium-low and let it cook uncovered, stirring occasionally, for 15-20 minutes or until slightly thickened.",
    "Serve hot as a main dish with whole grain bread."
